        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 6 at 5:21PM EDT by NWS Detroit/Pontiac MI</headline>
        <description>At 520 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Vassar, moving northeast at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Caro, Vassar, Cass City, Millington, Mayville, Fairgrove, Kingston,
Gagetown, Ellington, Wilmot, East Dayton, Deford, Colwood, and
Watrousville.

People attending Cass City Freedom Festival  should seek safe shelter
immediately!
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
